(* --- PASS: full_spec --- *)
<Test Unit> is a unit:
    plural is <Test Units>.
    abbreviation is "tu".

<count> is a unit:
    plural is <counts>.

<Temperature> is a number:
    valid values:
        35.0 °C ... 42.0 °C.
    meaning of <Temperature>:
        valid meanings:
            <yes>; <no>.
        38.0 °C ... 42.0 °C:
            meaning of value = <yes>.
            <High Fever> = <yes>.
        35.0 °C ... 37.9 °C:
            meaning of value = <no>.
            <High Fever> = <no>.
    question:
        ask "What is the patient's temperature?".

<High Fever> is an enumeration:
    valid values:
        <yes>; <no>.

<Pain Level> is a number:
    unit is <count>.
    question:
        style of question is <VisualAnalogScale>.
        question style is visual analogue scale:
            best value is 0 <count>.
            text for best value is "No Pain".
            worst value is 10 <counts>.
            text for worst value is "Worst Pain".
    
<Aspirin> is a drug:
    ingredients:
        <Acetylsalicylic Acid> 500 mg.
    dosage safety:
        maximum single dose = 1000 mg.
        maximum daily dose = 4000 mg.
        minimum time between doses = 4 hours.
    administration:
        form of administration is "Tablet".
    interactions:
        assess interaction with <Warfarin>:
            information "Warning: Risk of bleeding".

<Dr. House> is an addressee:
    contact information:
        email is "house@princeton-plainsboro.com".
        phone is "555-1234".
    after consent has been rejected:
         information "Patient rejected consent.".

<Dr. Wilson> is an addressee:
    contact information:
        email is "wilson@princeton-plainsboro.com".

<OncologyTeam> is an addressee group:
    grouped addressees are <Dr. House>; <Dr. Wilson>.
    order of contacting:
        contact all addressees in parallel.

<Treatment Plan> is a plan:
    before plan:
        ask <Temperature>.
        <Temperature> = 37.0 °C.
        
        assess <Temperature>:
            38.0 °C ... 42.0 °C:
                information "Fever detected.".
                <High Fever> = <yes>.
            35.0 °C ... 37.9 °C:
                information "Normal temperature.".
                <High Fever> = <no>.

        information to <Dr. House> "Assessment complete.".
        send information "Temp Log" <Temperature>.

    every 1 day for 7 days:
        assess trend of <Temperature>:
            "increase":
                information "Temperature is rising.".
            "decrease":
                information "Temperature is falling.".
            "stable":
                information "Temperature is stable.".

    change of <Pain Level>:
        context:
            timeframe: 24 hours ago ... now.
            data: <Pain Level>.
        
        assess count of <Pain Level>:
            3 <counts> ... 100 <counts>:
                information "Pain recorded multiple times today.".

