<testpoint> is a unit:
    plural is <testpoints>.
    abbreviation is "tp".

<Test Number> is a number:
    valid values:
        0 <testpoints> ... 100 <testpoints>.

<Test String> is a string.

<TestEnum> is an enumeration:
    valid values:
        <A>.
        <B>.
        <C>.

<Golden Plan> is a plan:
    before plan:
        <Test Number> = 42 <testpoint>.
        <Test String> = "Hello World".
        <TestEnum> = <A>.
        
        information "Number is " + <Test Number>.
        
        assess <Test Number>:
            1 <testpoint>:
                information "Single Point".
            41 <testpoints> ... 100 <testpoints>:
                information "High Value".
            0 <testpoints>:
                information "Low Value".
            2 <testpoints> ... 40 <testpoints>:
                information "Low Value".
                
        assess <TestEnum>:
            <A>:
                information "Enum is A".
            <B>; <C>:
                information "Either B or C".

